I noticed after while at algonquin college that
most of the passwords the password contained
the prefix "yA" followed by 6 numerals
i.e. "yA012345" so i decided to create another
wordlist using crunch and sed.
crunch 6 6 0123456789 | sed -e s/^/yA/ >st_word.lst
